2. github/spec-kit — https://github.com/github/spec-kit
   License: MIT
   Adopted in:
     - The 5-phase workflow naming (SPECIFY → CLARIFY → TASKS → ANALYZE → IMPLEMENT)
       reflected in templates/claude/commands/*.md slash commands.
     - templates/claude/commands/constitution.md       (from templates/commands/constitution.md)
       — `/constitution` slash command pattern adapted to the toolkit's
         two-tier model (constitution + ADR + invariants). Semver bumps
         + spec-kit's `extensions.yml` hook system intentionally dropped
         in favor of the existing ADR audit trail.
     - templates/agent_toolkit/constitution.md         (concept from memory/constitution.md)
       — "single slow-changing file with project principles" idea; agent-toolkit
         pre-fills it at install time via setup.py template substitution
